  "prompt": "How long can a milkshake last out of the fridge?",
  "response": "A milkshake should not be left out of the fridge for more than two hours. After this time, the risk of bacterial growth increases significantly, especially if the temperature is above 40\u00b0F (4\u00b0C). If the milkshake has been sitting in a warmer environment, it\u2019s best to err on the side of caution and discard it after one hour. Always prioritize food safety!",
